            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic and ginger are fragrant, add the <strong>jjigae stock </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until boiling</p><p>Add the <strong>grated carrot</strong> and<strong> tofu cubes</strong> and cook, covered, for 6-8 min further or until the tofu is warmed through – this is your <strong>Korean-style tofu jjigae stew</strong></p><p>Tip: If you’re still waiting on the rice to cook, reduce the heat to low and leave the stew to simmer</p>",
